## pixl CLI

When `pixl` CLI is installed, agents get persistent storage, AST-indexed search, and cost tracking.

| Command | What it does |
|---------|-------------|
| `pixl knowledge build --code` | Build AST-indexed code search (auto-runs on session start) |
| `pixl knowledge search <query>` | FTS5 semantic search across codebase |
| `pixl artifact list` | List build artifacts |
| `pixl cost summary` | Cost analytics: total, by-model, by-session |
| `pixl session list` | List past workflow sessions |
| `pixl workflow run` | Execute a workflow template |

Use `/intel` skill for ranked semantic search via the CLI. All features degrade gracefully to Glob/Grep when CLI is absent.

## Cross-Session Memory

```
.claude/memory/
├── decisions.jsonl      # Append-only decision log (injected on SessionStart)
├── instincts.jsonl      # Learned patterns from /continuous-learning
├── costs.jsonl          # Per-session token costs
└── sessions/            # Per-session summaries (last 3 loaded on start)
```

- **SessionStart hook** injects last 3 session summaries + last 10 decisions
- **Stop hook** captures git diff stats, modified files, task state
- Use `/session-wrap` at end of sessions to preserve decisions
- Use `/task-persist` to carry task state across sessions

## Hook Profiles

Control hook strictness via environment variable:

```bash
PIXL_HOOK_PROFILE=minimal claude    # fast exploratory (destructive blocking only)
PIXL_HOOK_PROFILE=standard claude   # default (+ formatting, TDD, skill checks)
PIXL_HOOK_PROFILE=strict claude     # all hooks (+ typecheck, console.log audit)
```

## Operational Rules

- **Explore → Plan → Implement → Commit** — use plan mode for multi-file changes
- **Skills over ad-hoc prompts** — if a skill exists for the task, use it
- **Frequent commits** — commit after each logical unit of work
- **Delegate to specialists** — use the agent routing table above to pick the right agent
- **Never build from scratch** — check studio stacks first; use `/saas-microservice` or `/website`
- **Use `/compact` proactively** — compact before starting unrelated tasks

